  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Forces | Calculate Forces</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_">Calculate Kinetostatic Forces Vectors</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Use the <text styleclass="VariableName-IT">Calculate Forces</text> button to <text styleclass="Body Text">silently</text> calculate <text styleclass="VariableName">Kinetostatic Forces Vectors</text> at each joint in each kinematically-defined chain.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Kinetostatic forces also calculate the <text styleclass="VariableName">Application</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> or </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Load Torque</text> that a servomotor and gearbox must make available at the output-shaft to drive the kinematic-chain.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Servomotors and gearboxes have inertia that must also accelerate, of course. To calculate the <text styleclass="VariableName">Total Torque</text> and size a servomotor and gearbox, use the <text styleclass="VariableName">Kinetostatic Torque-Speed dialog-box</text>.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="SeeAlso">See <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Forces-Show-Force-Vectors">Show Force Vectors</link><text styleclass="Body Text">. </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Dialog-Servo-Gearbox-Torque-Speed">Kinetostatic Servomotor and Gearbox selection</link></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="Standard" rowcount="5" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="vertical-align:middle; width:54px; height:38px;">
          <para styleclass="VariableName-IT" style="text-align:right;"><image src="Icon-CalculateForcesFB.png" scale="100.00%"></image></para>
        </td>
